markets.title: Will the **FDA authorize a pill** to fight COVID-19 by January 3, 2022?
markets.subtitle: By Jan 3, 2022
markets.expiration_value: The FDA has authorized the pill Paxlovid to fight COVID-19
markets.rules_primary: If the FDA issues a press release indicating it has authorized an oral antiviral to treat or prevent infection of COVID-19, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
Examples of potential oral antivirals include Lagevrio and Paxlovid.

If the event occurs, the market will close and determine one day following at 10:00 AM.
